==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equimultiple
<hw>E`qui*mul"ti*ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Equi-</ets> + <ets>multiple</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧quimultiple</ets>.]</ety> <def>Multiplied by the same
number or quantity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equimultiple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Equimultiple
<hw>E`qui*mul"ti*ple</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>One of
the products arising from the multiplication of two or more quantities
by the same number or quantity. Thus, seven times 2, or 14, and seven
times 4, or 28, are <xex>equimultiples</xex> of 2 and 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equinal</ent>⟦br⟧
